<TITLE> GOVERNMENT CONDITIONS FOR ABDUL JALIL </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 2 (bdnews24.com)The government has laid out a series of conditions for Awami League general secretary Abdul Jalil to comply with for his 30-day parole and treatment abroad, according a statement released by the Press Information Department Sunday. If Jalil goes abroad for treatment, he or his relatives must inform Bangladesh mission there about his health every three days. Jalil must not take part in political, business or any other activities. He is not allowed to make contact any organisation or person except on health grounds. Soon after his treatment, the AL leader must inform the government and return home. If allowed to go to a foreign country for treatment, he cannot travel to a third from there. The government stressed that violations of the conditions will lead to scrapping of the parole decision.
